I ventured to remind the good man of my own business also;
whereupon, with an expression of, if anything, increased dryness, he
again asked me to wait.

In fact, during the two
weeks of my absence I had felt far more at my ease than I did now, on
the day of my return;

So now she showed me more attention when talking to me;
while, for his part, the Frenchman approached me, and asked outright if
it had been my own money that I had lost.

The Frenchman had
listened to me contemptuously, with a slight protruding of his eyes;
but, he could not have understood very much of my harangue.

Of
course, at the time I took them half in jest and half as a challenge;
yet, she had spoken them with great seriousness.

Last night he said that, for some reason or
another, it behoved him to  move with especial care at present; 
wherefore, he was feeling nervous.

Of course
this was a rare occasion an occasion on which zero had turned up no
less than three times within a dozen rounds;

De
Griers smoothed his hair, and twisted his angry face into a smile into
the mean, studiedly polite French smile which I so detested;

The rest of the day Mlle.
spent in probing the Prince, and trying to make him declare himself;
but in this she made a woeful mistake.

All day until eight o clock that evening did she play;
and, though I personally did not witness her exploits, I learnt of them
later through report.

Also, I could not but marvel at the way in which,
for seven or eight hours at a stretch, she sat in that chair of hers,
almost never leaving the table.

But as soon as ever he saw me at
the door he came towards me in such a curious manner that involuntarily
I retreated a step, and was for leaving the room;

Every moment Mlle.
Polina kept telling me to open the window and see if you were there;
after which she always smiled."

Every now and then, also, some particular word would please him;
whereupon he would repeat it a hundred times in the day even though the
word happened to express neither his thoughts nor his feelings.
